---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Equity Guardians collects, uses, shares, and protects the personal information of homeowners, partner realtors, and site visitors."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    description="How we collect, use, share, and protect personal information."
  />

  <section>
    <div class="container legal-wrap">
      <div class="legal-meta reveal">
        <p><strong>Effective date:</strong> July 4, 2026 <span class="sep">·</span> <strong>Last updated:</strong> July 6, 2026</p>
      </div>

      <article class="legal-body reveal">
        <p>
          Equity Guardians LLC (&ldquo;Equity Guardians,&rdquo; &ldquo;EG,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo;
          &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy
          explains how we collect, use, share, and protect personal information when you visit
          <a href="https://www.equityguardians.com">www.equityguardians.com</a> (the &ldquo;Site&rdquo;),
          when you are offered or enrolled in the Equity Guardians program (the &ldquo;Program&rdquo;),
          or when you otherwise interact with us.
        </p>
        <p>
          Equity Guardians is a home-equity protection service for homeowners. We are not a law
          firm and do not provide legal advice, and we are not a real estate brokerage. The Program
          is delivered through independently licensed attorneys, licensed real estate professionals,
          and an EG case manager who coordinates. This Policy works together with our Terms of
          Service and, for enrolled homeowners and partner real estate professionals, with the
          Member Service Agreement and the Partner Realtor Services Agreement.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Who This Policy Covers</h2>
        <p>This Policy applies to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>homeowners who are offered or enrolled in the Program (&ldquo;Members&rdquo;);</li>
          <li>real estate professionals who partner with us (&ldquo;Partner Realtors&rdquo;); and</li>
          <li>visitors to the Site.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Information you provide to us.</strong> Your name and contact details; the
          property address; information about your mortgage, loan servicer, and financial
          circumstances, including any financial hardship; information you share when you request
          help or communicate with us; and the consents and authorizations you give us.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Information we receive from Partner Realtors.</strong> When a Partner Realtor
          enrolls you, we may receive your contact information and details about your home
          purchase and closing needed to provide the Program.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Information from other third parties.</strong> We may receive information from
          mortgage servicers and lenders, from the independent attorneys who represent you, from
          curated savings and cashback partners, and from public records, in each case as needed
          to deliver the Program.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Information collected automatically on the Site.</strong> When you use the Site
          we may collect device and browser information, IP address, pages viewed, and similar
          usage data through cookies and comparable technologies.
        </p>

        <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>We use personal information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            deliver and coordinate the Program, including equity-building guidance, foreclosure
            protection, curated savings, realtor-led pre-foreclosure sale support, foreclosure
            recovery, and case management;
          </li>
          <li>
            connect you with an appropriate independent attorney and arrange payment of the
            attorney&rsquo;s retainer through the Program;
          </li>
          <li>
            prepare and send the value-added correspondence (at least once each calendar quarter)
            on your Partner Realtor&rsquo;s behalf;
          </li>
          <li>communicate with you and respond to your requests;</li>
          <li>operate, maintain, secure, and improve the Site and our services; and</li>
          <li>comply with legal, regulatory, and recordkeeping obligations.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How We Share Information</h2>
        <p>We share personal information only as needed to run the Program and operate our business, including with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>the Legal Team, the independent attorneys who advise and represent you;</li>
          <li>your Partner Realtor, for the real estate services and attributed correspondence provided on their behalf;</li>
          <li>the Case Manager and EG personnel who coordinate your services;</li>
          <li>mortgage servicers and lenders, with your authorization, as needed to help with your loan;</li>
          <li>curated savings and cashback partners, to make offers available to you;</li>
          <li>service providers and vendors who support our operations under confidentiality obligations;</li>
          <li>legal and compliance recipients, when required by law, subpoena, or to protect rights and safety; and</li>
          <li>a successor in the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, subject to this Policy.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell your personal information.</p>

        <h2>5. Financial Information</h2>
        <p>
          Because the Program involves your mortgage and financial circumstances, we may collect
          and handle nonpublic personal financial information. We handle that information
          consistent with applicable financial-privacy law.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Marketing Communications and Your Choices</h2>
        <p>
          We (and, on their behalf, your Partner Realtor) may send you newsletters, educational
          content, and savings or discount offers.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Email.</strong> Every marketing email includes an unsubscribe link, consistent
          with the CAN-SPAM Act.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Text messages and calls.</strong> We contact you by text or automated call only
          with your consent; you may opt out at any time (for example, by replying STOP),
          consistent with the Telephone Consumer Protection Act (TCPA).
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Essential messages.</strong> Even if you opt out of marketing, we may still send
          you service, transaction, and legally required messages.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
        <p>
          The Site may use cookies and similar technologies to operate the Site, remember
          preferences, and understand usage. You can control cookies through your browser settings.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain personal information for as long as needed to provide the Program, which, for
          enrolled Members, generally continues for the life of the deed of trust, and afterward
          as needed for legal, regulatory, and recordkeeping purposes, after which we delete or
          de-identify it.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards designed to protect
          personal information. No method of transmission or storage is completely secure, and we
          cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access, correct, delete, or
          receive a copy of your personal information, and to opt out of certain uses. Residents
          of certain states, for example California, Colorado, Connecticut, and Virginia, may have
          additional rights under state privacy laws. To exercise a right, contact us using
          Section 14. We will not discriminate against you for exercising your rights.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Children&rsquo;s Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          The Site and Program are not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly
          collect personal information from them. If you believe a child has provided us
          information, contact us and we will delete it.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Third-Party Links and Services</h2>
        <p>
          The Site may link to third-party websites and services we do not control. This Policy
          does not apply to those third parties, and we are not responsible for their privacy
          practices.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the &ldquo;Last
          updated&rdquo; date above and, where appropriate, provide additional notice.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          Equity Guardians LLC<br />
          1 World Trade Center, 85th Floor, New York, NY 10007<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:admin@equityguardians.com">admin@equityguardians.com</a><br />
          Phone: <a href="tel:+18883640999">(888) 364-0999</a>
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-wrap {
    max-width: 780px;
    padding-block: 3rem 5rem;
  }
  .legal-meta {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: #FBF7EE;
    border: 1px solid #E9DEC1;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--slate-700);
  }
  .legal-meta p { margin: 0; }
  .legal-meta .sep { color: var(--teal-500); margin: 0 0.35rem; }
  .legal-body {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--slate-700);
  }
  .legal-body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--navy-900);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
  }
  .legal-body p { margin: 0 0 1.1rem; }
  .legal-body ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.4rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }
  .legal-body li { margin-bottom: 0.55rem; }
  .legal-body a { color: var(--teal-700); text-decoration: underline; }
  .legal-body a:hover { color: var(--teal-500); }
  .legal-body strong { color: var(--navy-900); }
</style>
